<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-32-1395 </DOCNO><TEXT>Cogeneration for commercial applications, particularly gas-fueled, hasa bright future. Besides the fundamental thermodynamics, which have alwaysfavored cogeneration, future electric and gas prices, ample suppliesof natural gas, and the electric industry's coming need for new generatingcapacity all bode well for the growth of cogeneration as a significantcontributor to future energy efficiency.</TEXT></DOC>